    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1909-10-27T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1909-10-27T00:00:00-05:00" n="243"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d243">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 5869/236.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">French Ambassador</gloss> to the <gloss
                            type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Translation.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">French Embassy</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1909-10-27">
                            <hi rend="italic">October 27, 1909</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Mr. Secretary of State</hi>: My Government has just advised
                    me that the last day on which the commercial arrangements recently denounced <pb
                        facs="0326" n="254" xml:id="pg_254"/> by the United States Government can be
                    applied happening to be a Sunday, the necessary arrangements have been made to
                    keep the French customhouse open on that day.</p>
                <p>I have, in consequence, the honor to inform your excellency that American imports
                    will enjoy the benefits of the present order for products arrived and entered in
                    France on the 31st of this month.</p>
                <p>Be pleased, etc,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Jusserand.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
